# RSS Scraper - Home Assignment for sendCloud

Author: Maor Avitan

## Overview

RSS Scraper is a FastAPI application that allows you to scrape and manage RSS feeds and their items. This README provides instructions for setting up and running the application locally and inside a Docker container.

## Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed:

- Python (>= 3.6)
- Docker (if you want to run the app in a container)

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/maoravitan/rss-scraper.git
   cd rss-scraper
Create a virtual environment (optional but recommended):

bash
Copy code
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
Install the required packages:

bash
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt
Configuration
Copy the sample environment file and customize it as needed:

bash
Copy code
cp .env.example .env
Edit .env to configure your database connection and other settings.

Running the App Locally
To run the application locally:

bash
Copy code
uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
You can access the app at http://localhost:8000.

Building and Running in Docker
To build and run the application inside a Docker container:

Build the Docker image:

bash
Copy code
docker build -t rss-scraper .
Run the Docker container:

bash
Copy code
docker run -d -p 8000:80 --name rss-scraper-app rss-scraper
You can access the app at http://localhost:8000.

API Documentation
Swagger UI is available at /docs when running the app. You can use it to explore and test the APIs provided by the application.

